<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="827" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d827">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Moffat</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-31"><hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Moffat reports the unanimous election of Estrada and Diaz as
                            president and vice president respectively. He says there is intense
                            enthusiasm.</p>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[To be continued in <ref target="frus1911">Foreign Relations,
                                    1911</ref>.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>